# PROJEKT AI WEBSITE - EXTRA MEDIUM STYLE ENFORCEMENT
# These rules MUST be followed for all code changes to maintain design consistency

## DESIGN SYSTEM ENFORCEMENT

### FORBIDDEN STYLING PATTERNS
- NO blue gradients or any gradients whatsoever
- NO rounded corners (border-radius) except for circles (50% only)
- NO box-shadows except for subtle ones (max 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1))
- NO hover animations or transform effects
- NO bright colors or vibrant accents
- NO heavy borders (max 1px solid)
- NO complex animations or transitions
- NO background patterns or textures

### REQUIRED COLOR PALETTE
- Primary background: #ffffff (white)
- Secondary background: #f8f9fa (light gray)
- Dark sections: #1a1a1a (near black)
- Text primary: #1a1a1a (dark)
- Text secondary: #666666 (medium gray)
- Borders: #e9ecef (light gray)
- NEVER use: blue, bright colors, multiple accent colors

### TYPOGRAPHY RULES
- Font family: Inter ONLY (weights: 300, 400, 500, 600, 700, 800)
- Headings: font-weight 700, letter-spacing -0.02em
- Body text: font-weight 400, line-height 1.6
- NO decorative fonts or script fonts
- NO text shadows or effects

### LAYOUT CONSTRAINTS
- Container max-width: 1200px
- Padding: 20px (sides), 100px (sections)
- Grid gaps: 30px-60px maximum
- NO complex nested grids
- Simple flexbox or CSS Grid only

### COMPONENT STYLING RULES
- Buttons: Simple rectangles, solid colors, no gradients
- Cards: White background, minimal shadow, clean edges
- Forms: Clean inputs, no fancy styling
- Navigation: Simple, horizontal, minimal
- Logo sections: Grayscale, simple horizontal layout

### CSS STANDARDS ENFORCEMENT
- Use ONLY /assets/css/main.css and /assets/css/case-study.css
- NO inline styles except for minor adjustments
- NO external CSS frameworks (Bootstrap, Tailwind, etc.)
- NO CSS-in-JS solutions

### RESPONSIVE DESIGN
- Mobile-first approach
- Simple breakpoints: 768px, 1024px
- NO complex responsive animations
- Stack elements simply on mobile

## CODE QUALITY RULES

### HTML STRUCTURE
- Semantic HTML5 elements required
- Clean, readable structure
- Proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3)
- Accessible alt text for images

### PERFORMANCE REQUIREMENTS
- Optimize all images before use
- Minimize CSS and JS
- NO unnecessary dependencies
- Fast loading times priority

### FILE ORGANIZATION
- Images in /assets/img/ with proper naming
- SVG logos in /assets/img/software-logos/
- NO duplicate files or unused assets

## CONTENT GUIDELINES

### TONE AND MESSAGING
- Personal expertise focus (20+ years experience)
- Individual specialist, NOT agency language
- Music industry specific terminology
- Professional but approachable tone

### SECTION STRUCTURE
- Hero: Simple, centered, clean
- Services: Grid layout, numbered items
- About: Personal story, individual focus
- FAQ: Sanny-style structure exactly
- Technology: Simple horizontal logo row

## DEPLOYMENT RULES

### BUILD PROCESS
- Always run npm run build:prod before deploy
- Test on multiple devices
- Validate HTML and CSS
- Check loading performance

### GIT WORKFLOW
- Descriptive commit messages
- Test changes locally first
- Deploy via git push (auto-deploys to Netlify)

## STRICT PROHIBITIONS

### NEVER ALLOW
- Blue color schemes or gradients
- Complex animations or micro-interactions
- Heavy visual effects or shadows
- Rounded corners except for circles
- Multiple accent colors
- Decorative elements or patterns
- Agency-style language or team references
- Legacy CSS files (portfolio-dark.css, style.css, etc.)

### ALWAYS REQUIRE
- Extra Medium minimalist aesthetic
- Clean, professional appearance
- Fast loading and performance
- Mobile responsiveness
- Accessibility compliance
- Personal branding consistency

## EMERGENCY OVERRIDES
Only in extreme cases where client specifically requests deviation:
1. Document the reason in commit message
2. Update this .cursorrules file
3. Ensure change aligns with overall brand
4. Test thoroughly before deployment

